CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 7, reads: "Women Campaign For YMCA - The 'Satellites,' under Co-Pilot Mrs. Martha Talley, are 'out of this world' in Centre Ave. YMCA membership campaign. At Monday's 'Report Night,' they rolled into outer space with a total of 377 members and 2,771 1/2 points.  Crew members are, left to right: Barbara Robinson, Mmes. Martha Tate, Talley and Ulysses Williams; William A. Arvin, general chairman of the drive, and Mmes. Charles Robinson, Louise Fountain and Doris High.  The next 'Report Night' is Feb. 17, at 6 P.M. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Barbara Robinson, Martha Tate, Martha Talley, Mrs. Ulysses Williams, William A. Arvin, Mrs. Charles Robinson, Louise Fountain, and Doris High, posed in front of membership toteboard in Centre Avenue YMCA
